## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="37e50-102">Una instancia de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> se crea cuando el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> objeto genera un `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` eventos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> object raises an `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="37e50-103">Para obtener información relacionada con un `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` eventos, obtener acceso a las siguientes propiedades en el controlador del evento:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-103">To obtain information related to an `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` event, access the following properties in the handler for the event:</span></span>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="37e50-104">El <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> propiedad hace referencia a la posición del dispositivo de entrada en su secuencia de audio generado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-104">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> property references the input device's position in its generated audio stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="37e50-105">Por el contrario, el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> propiedad hace referencia a la posición del reconocedor dentro de su entrada de audio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-105">By contrast, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> property references the recognizer's position within its audio input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="37e50-106">Estas posiciones pueden ser diferentes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-106">These positions can be different.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="37e50-107">Para obtener más información, consulte [mediante eventos de reconocimiento de voz](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-107">For more information, see [Using Speech Recognition Events](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="37e50-108">El <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A> propiedad indica qué problema se ha producido.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-108">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A> property indicates which problem occurred.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="37e50-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> se deriva de <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="37e50-110">En el ejemplo siguiente se define un controlador de eventos que recopila información sobre un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioSignalProblemOccurred> eventos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="37e50-110">The following example defines an event handler that gathers information about an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioSignalProblemOccurred> event.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.  
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the AudioSignalProblemOccurred event.  
  sre.AudioSignalProblemOccurred += new EventHandler<AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs>(sre_AudioSignalProblemOccurred);  
}  
  
// Gather information when the AudioSignalProblemOccurred event is raised.  
void sre_AudioSignalProblemOccurred(object sender, AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs e)  
{  
  StringBuilder details = new StringBuilder();  
  
  details.AppendLine("Audio signal problem information:");  
  details.AppendFormat(  
    " Audio level:               {0}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Audio position:            {1}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Audio signal problem:      {2}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Recognition engine audio position: {3}" + Environment.NewLine,  
    e.AudioLevel, e.AudioPosition,  e.AudioSignalProblem,  
    e.RecognizerAudioPosition);  
  
  // Insert additional event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
